modules.description: Provides functions to parse and manipulate static content without executing embedded code, including extracting and sanitizing markup fragments. Works with strings and abstract syntax trees representing content structures. Used to preprocess documentation and web assets for safe inclusion in generated outputs.

Handles command substitution by intercepting and modifying rewrite trees to block shell command execution. Operates on attribute lists and abstract syntax trees generated by Xtmpl.Rewrite. Prevents unintended command runs in template processing by altering the evaluation flow.
